unittitle.value: Gay and Lesbian Pulp Fiction Collection

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: American queer culture saw some of its earliest mass expression in the pulp fiction market starting around the end of World War II. The collection includes a substantial sampling of the gay pulp fiction genre from the 1950's to the 1980's.

p.value: Open to researchers. Appointments are necessary for the use of manuscript and archival collections.

Published citations should take the following form:
